29
00:02:26.000 --> 00:02:36.000
Pearl Milk Tea or bubble tea, as it's often called, was invented in 1987 by Taiwanese T-Shop owner Liu Han-Chir.

30
00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:42.000
The bubbles in a glass of bubble tea are made from balls of a chewy starch called tapioca.

31
00:02:42.000 --> 00:02:48.000
Food which is chewy needs to be chewed a lot before it becomes soft enough to swallow.

32
00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:54.000
It's these tapioca balls, which give bubble tea its name. You might say their bubble tea's signature

33
00:02:54.000 --> 00:03:00.000
ingredient, their special feature for which something is particularly known.

34
00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:04.000
For example, Payaya is the signature dish of Spain.

35
00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:08.000
What's more, because tapioca doesn't have a strong taste?

36
00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:16.000
Different flavours can be added, making bubble tea an innovative, meaning new and original drink.

37
00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:22.000
Liu Han-Chir's invention was inspired by a trip to Japan, where he saw people enjoying

38
00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:30.000
iced milk tea on a hot summer's day. When he added tapioca balls, which he found in a local market on his return

39
00:03:30.000 --> 00:03:36.000
to Taiwan, the bubbley new beverage was born. But it was only when famous international celebrities,

40
00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:42.000
including basketball player Michael Jordan and movie star Jackie Chan, started visiting his T-Shop,

41
00:03:42.000 --> 00:03:48.000
that Liu Han-Chir's bubble tea began a revolution in the tea drinking world.

42
00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:54.000
Here is Liu Han-Chir, telling more to BBC World Service Program witness history.

43
00:03:54.000 --> 00:03:56.000
So it's your summer day.

44
00:03:56.000 --> 00:04:02.000
Pro-muk tea got huge media coverage and it spread like wildfire, but I always say, we have many

45
00:04:02.000 --> 00:04:10.000
other products, and the reason Pro-muk tea became so popular was pure luck. It was a miracle.

46
00:04:10.000 --> 00:04:16.000
Thanks to its celebrity fans, Liu Han-Chir's bubble tea became an international best seller,

47
00:04:16.000 --> 00:04:24.000
a news of his exciting new drink spread like wildfire, an idea meaning it became quickly known

48
00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:30.000
