49
00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:36.000
bubble tea spread to neighbouring countries like South Korea and China, and then to the rest of the world.

50
00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:42.000
For Liu Han-Chir, it was a miracle, a very lucky event that is surprising and unexpected.

51
00:04:42.000 --> 00:04:50.000
It's great to hear about something that gives a modern twist to a drink that's part of a country's traditional culture.

52
00:04:50.000 --> 00:04:52.000
Maybe that's what we need here in Britain too.

53
00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:58.000
Yes, your question was about the fact that nowadays more people in Britain prefer coffee than tea.

54
00:04:58.000 --> 00:05:00.000
I think it's time you reveal the answer.

55
00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:08.000
Right, I asked you what percentage of breads still regularly prefer drinking tea over coffee,

56
00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:14.000
